a.title: Webhooks
a.desc: Webhooks are a way to interact with Windmill using standard web technologies.

a.title: Auto-Generated UIs
a.desc: Windmill automatically generates user interfaces (UIs) for scripts and flows based on their parameters.

a.title: Schedules
a.desc: Windmill provides the same set of features as CRON, but with a user interface and control panels.

a.title: Public Apps
a.desc: Windmill apps are custom-made user interfaces meant to interact with scripts and flows.

a.title: Suspend and Approval / Prompts
a.desc: Flows can be suspended until resumed or canceled event(s) are received.

a.title: Data Pipelines
a.desc: Windmill streamlines the creation of data pipelines that are not only fast and reliable but also straightforward to construct.

a.title: App Editor
a.desc: The app editor is a low-code builder to create custom User Interfaces with a mix of drag-and-drop and code.

a.title: Flow Editor
a.desc: Windmill's Flow Editor allows you to build flows with a low-code builder.
